This update for openssh fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2021-28041: Fixed double free in ssh-agent (bsc#1183137).

notes.text: ssh-agent in OpenSSH before 8.5 has a double free that may be relevant in a few less-common scenarios, such as unconstrained agent-socket access on a legacy operating system, or the forwarding of an agent to an attacker-controlled host.
